  "text": "where the primed elements are the noise-error-corrected Stokes parameters and jn p j 2 is the noise power measured in the p'th polarization channel. The noise correction improves DOPU measurements in particular for weak signals close to the noise floor (SNR < 10 dB in reflectivity images). [CITATION_1] Now, as in many PS-OCT designs, the optical and electronical layout of the two polarization detection channels is identical, we may assume that jn H j 2 ≈ jn V j 2 . As a consequence, Q 0 ≈ Q such that only I 0 is left to be corrected for the additive noise error. By plugging the expression for I 0 into Eq. (1) and using the relation SNR ¼ I∕ðjn H j 2 þ jn V j 2 Þ for the SNR of the PS-OCT reflectivity signal, the expression for the noisecorrected quantity DOPU′ simplifies to read E Q -T A R G E T ; t e m p : i n t r a l i n k -; e 0 0 2 ; 3 2 6 ; 4 5 6",
